{{also|Puer}} ==English==
===Pronunciation=== {{rfap||UK}} {{rfap||US}}
===Etymology=== Perhaps from {{etyl|fr|en}}.
===Noun=== {{en-noun|-}}
# {{context|chiefly|historical|lang=en}} [[canine|Canine]] [[faeces]] used as a [[lye]] in [[tanning]]. #* '''1903''', Henry Richardson Proctor, ''The principles of leather manufacture'', page 174: #*: {{...}} The bacteria of fresh dog-dung were not found to possess a satisfactory puering effect, but those from dung with had been fermented a month (as in practice) have a result nearly equal to actual '''puer'''. #* '''2009''', Tony Covington, ''Tanning Chemistry: The Science of Leather'', page 166: #*: {{...}} it was about 50 years before the use of '''puer''' was discontinued, at least in Europe.
===Anagrams=== * [[Peru#English|Peru]], [[Prue#English|Prue]], [[pure#English|pure]], [[re-up#English|re-up]]
