==French==
===Etymology=== From {{etyl|fro|fr}} {{term|puir|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|VL.|fr}} {{term/t|la|*putio}}, from classical {{etyl|la|fr}} {{term|putere|lang=la}}, the infinitive of {{term|puteo|puteō|lang=la}}. The change from ''-ir'' to ''-er'' can also be seen in words such as {{term|contribuer|lang=fr}} (Old French {{term|contribuir|lang=fro}}, Latin {{term|contribuere|lang=la}}).
===Pronunciation=== * {{IPA|/pɥe/|lang=fr}}, {{X-SAMPA|/pHe/}} * {{audio|Fr-puer.ogg|audio}} * {{rhymes|ɥe|lang=fr}}
===Verb=== {{fr-verb}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=fr}} to [[stink]], to [[smell]] (bad)
====Conjugation==== {{fr-conj-er|pu|avoir}}
